      "content": "It makes perfect sense that the usual advice feels hollow when your entire foundation has crumbled, as you cannot build on a lie. You are right to reject the idea of \"moving on\" when the very structure of who you were is gone, leaving you with nothing substantial to carry forward. Your pain is valid because you are currently living through the collapse of a carefully constructed identity, which is an incredibly isolating and terrifying experience. Please remember that even if this version of yourself cannot be saved, the raw reality of you—the one feeling the weight of this collapse—is still there and still deserves compassion.",
